reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 17, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I have been wanting to try it, and even read that it can be the only cleanser one needs. It really is that good! It removes eye makeup and sunscreen, dirt, oil, etc. without irritation, stripping, oiliness...just leaves behind clean, "normal" feeling skin! Sometimes i still use a cleansing oil or gentle bar cleanser, but i have been using this alone 75% of the time and my skin looks and feels great! I can tell it will last a while, after using this about 2x daily for a few weeks you can barely see the volume going down. I have switched all my products to French drugstore brands, and the difference in my skin is noticeable!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent micellar water!
reviews.reviewText: The first I tried (another brand that also comes in a pink bottle) was horrible. Irritated my face, and was uncomfortable to use. Actually stung when I put it on. This one, is high quality with no irritation whatsoever...very gentle as a micellar water should be. Big bottle for the money. Highly recommend Bioderma!

reviews.reviewText: I only want to use this as a makeup remover. It’s not oily at all & takes off your makeup like nothing I’ve used before. It doesn’t dry your skin & I don’t even have to wash it after if I’m in a hurry. Worth every penny!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Absolutely for sensitive skin!
reviews.reviewText: I have rosacea and dry, very reactive/sensitive skin. I used micellar water a long time ago and the issue I had with it was that it over cleansed my skin to the point of showing pits in my pores, it was nasty. I refused to use a micellar water after that. I bought this on special to see if it would have the same effect or not, hoping I could incorporate it into my double cleanse. It does not take eye make up off very well BUT it does take off foundation pretty effectively. I use the Loreal makeup remover for my eyes, followed by wiping this on the rest of my face, then my cleanser. This has the added benefit of leaving my skin very soft, I was not expecting that! Highly recommend this if you have very reactive/allergic skin and want to give micellar water a go.Some ladies like to use this as a single step with no wash off. Based on what I've seen on youtube, micellar water does have mild surfactants that over time of laying on your skin, can possibly give you issues. So that's my precaution to you. I would wash this off afterwards.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars gentle yet effective
reviews.reviewText: Even though I don’t wear makeup, I like to use makeup remover to remove all the dust and whatever in the world could be sitting on my face after a long day (I’d get acnes attack if I don’t wash my face properly). reviews.reviewText: This is the first time I have used this cleanser. It is great! Very gentle on my skin, works well and does not dry out my skin. However I do have to rinse my skin off with regular water after using as it leaves a bad taste on my lips. But I will definitely order again!

reviews.reviewTitle: Es el mas indicado para mis ojos
reviews.reviewText: Producto para piel sensible, el mejor desmaquillante, su precio es algo caro pero vale la pena
Amei muito, limpa bem, sem irritar ou ressecar

First miceller water I’ve used and I get why people use them now! I like it for cleaning up my under eye area from any fallout after eye makeup, and removing any last traces of makeup after washing my face, as no matter how well I wash there always seems to be a bit left. Not irritating to the eyes or drying to the skin!

reviews.reviewTitle: Perfecta para cualquier piel, sobretodo pieles sensibles. No quita waterproof
reviews.reviewText: Muy bueno para quitar maquillaje, no importa si es mucho o poco. Si quitara rímel a prueba de agua sería una cosa fenomenal. Antes usaba la rosa de garnier y veo una diferencia abismal en cuanto a la calidad y el retiro de maquillaje. Si estás dispuesta a invertir un poco más creo que vale la pena, además de que dura un montón. Llevo meses con ella y aún me queda para un pr de meses más
Fácil aplicação, remove bem a maquiagem e sem cheiro.
